People cross a destroyed bridge as they evacuate the city of Irpin, northwest of Kyiv, during heavy shelling and bombing. AFP/Aris Messinis KIEV - A partial ceasefire in Ukraine collapsed just hours after it was implemented. Russia and Ukraine are blaming each other for violating the truce. READ: War in Ukraine | Russia declares partial ceasefire Ukraine says Russia began the shelling, while Russia says fire was opened from inside the cities. The ceasefire was agreed to so about 200,000 civilians in the two besieged cities could leave. WATCH: War in Ukraine | Temporary ceasefire in effect It was part of an agreement on humanitarian corridors. But, the resumption of fighting saw residents of Mariupol scrambling back to shelters. The city has been cut off from food, water and electricity.